Manthena Satyanarayana Raju - prominent Indian naturopath and wellness advocate.
In this Telugu podcast episode, a renowned naturopathy and preventive health expert breaks down food habits, fasting, preventive healthcare, blood tests, AMR, detox, and natural healing, explaining how modern lifestyles are silently damaging our bodies and how to reverse it.
The conversation begins with simple yet powerful ideas around listening to your body, eating right for your age, understanding medical reports, and knowing when health tests truly matter, backed by ICMR data and real-world observation. From intermittent fasting vs traditional fasting, Shivarathri and Kedarnath references, to giving the body a weekly rest day, the myths around fasting, diet trends, and enjoyment vs self-care are unpacked with clarity.
We also dive into modern health traps like tablet culture,drug-resistance, social media food influence, packaged foods entering Indian homes, and why fruits, sunlight, rest, and recovery matter more than shortcuts. Using sharp analogies from animals, fever, and nature, he explains why humans break down early while natural systems don‚Äôt.
Touching upon naturopathy, yoga, ashram life, and the philosophies of Gandhi, and Morarji Desai, this episode stays practical, light, and deeply relevant. item.title: THIS Is How Netflix Actually Works!
item.description:
You tap play on Netflix, and in less than a second, an episode starts streaming.
That‚Äôs not magic, that‚Äôs TCP/IP doing its job perfectly.
This is how it works, layer by layer.
1. Network Access Layer: This is the entry point. Your device connects to the internet using Wi-Fi or mobile data. If this layer fails, nothing even starts.
2. Internet Layer: Your device has an IP address; Netflix servers have theirs. Routers read these addresses and guide your request across the internet until it reaches Netflix.
3. Transport Layer: The video doesn‚Äôt travel as one big file. It‚Äôs split into small packets that arrive in random order. Your device‚Äôs job is to collect and organize them.
4. Application Layer: This layer handles communication rules. DNS finds the right Netflix server, HTTPS delivers the video securely, and keeps everything protected.
All layers work together so Netflix can load the UI, control, subtitles, and decode the video, so it can play the episode smoothly.
Want more easy explainers like this? Comment down the topic, and I‚Äôll cover it in the future shorts.
Save this for later, and share it with your friends who might find it helpful.

item.title: Why The IIT or IIM Tag Is NOT Everything?! | Vishakha Sadhwani
item.description:
When I started working as a waitress after moving to the US for higher education, I never thought that one day I would be working at companies like NVIDIA or Google. At that point, life was simple.
Pay the bills. Figure things out. Keep going. And the most surprising part is that I never really planned to be in the cloud space.
When I got my first job, I wanted to build applications using Java. That was the goal.
But instead, I ended up working on a cloud migration project.
That one project slowly changed the direction of my career.
And now, here I am today. Not because everything was planned perfectly, but because I kept learning, adapting, and moving forward when opportunities showed up.
If you could relate to this, you‚Äôre not alone. Share this with someone who might need to hear it today.

item.title: ü§©ü•≥ üéâ SPECIAL PODCAST - RAW TALKS | Ft. Chandra Bose Garu | Telugu Podcast
item.description:
To continue the research, do check this sheet: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1QWzUzqweV9MPp5n0ngcoEN-lK7Wg62zPcsaG8-X9HXw/edit?usp=sharing
Kanukuntla Subhash Chandrabose‚ÄîIndian lyricist and singer, Oscar Winner, who works in Telugu cinema.
In this Telugu podcast episode, legendary lyricist Chandrabose opens up about his extraordinary journey through words, music, and emotion, from writing over 3600 Telugu film songs to witnessing history with RRR winning India‚Äôs first Oscar. He shares what the Oscar moment truly felt like, how global legends like Diane Warren predicted the win even before nominations, and why that recognition mattered not just to a film, but to Indian storytelling itself.
From classics like ‚ÄúNenu Unnanani,‚Äù ‚ÄúPanchadara Bomma,‚Äù ‚ÄúRaju Nuvve,‚Äù ‚ÄúChiru Chiru Chinukai,‚Äù ‚ÄúKumkumala,‚Äù and ‚ÄúOo Antava‚Äù, Chandrabose reflects on how songs are born during train journeys, petrol bunk stops, late-night thoughts, and deeply personal moments. He speaks about his writing philosophy shaped by his illiterate mother who loved songs, the influence of Acharya Aatreya, Sri Sri, Sirivennela Seetharama Sastry, and how simplicity in language is far more powerful than complexity. For him, people have always been the real metrics, long before views, charts, or algorithms existed.
The conversation explores the evolution of Telugu cinema music, the changing perception of Special songs (item songs), the discipline behind writing without repetition, the pain of rejection, and the patience it takes for recognition to arrive sometimes decades later. He also breaks down the reality of royalties, IPRS, intellectual property rights, and how songs continue to earn and travel far beyond cinema screens.
Touching upon his BTech background, childhood stories, love for language, and the emotional connection with ‚Äúamma,‚Äù this episode blends craft, struggle, and inspiration. It is a warm, honest, and deeply musical conversation that flows with humour, nostalgia, and powerful life lessons, making it as enjoyable as it is insightful for anyone who loves Telugu songs, cinema, and stories that stay with you long after the music fades. . item.description:
A new show has been added to showRSS: The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City.

The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City takes viewers into an undiscovered world that is about so much more than religion, although the Mormon church is undeniably engrained in the culture. In the majestic mountains of Utah is a hidden social circle made up of successful women who have created their own paradise filled with luxury homes, shopping sprees and multi-million-dollar businesses and brands. They have mastered running wildly successful enterprises by day and enjoy apr√®s ski at the finest resorts by night, all the while raising extraordinary and unconventional families. Here perfection is not an aspiration, it's a mandate. They hold themselves and each other to an extremely high standard and never hold back when things go sideways, but lord knows they are always there for each other when they need it most.

item.title: WHY Your Resume Is NOT Getting Shortlisted?! | Vishakha Sadhwani
item.description:
In this short, I‚Äôll share the exact resume format you need to get shortlisted in the top tech companies effortlessly in 2026.
Your resume doesn‚Äôt need to be complicated. It just needs the right structure.
Start with Education. Keep it simple: degree, university, year, GPA. Add coursework only if you‚Äôre applying for entry-level roles.
Then add Technical Skills. Put your strongest tools and platforms up front. The right keywords matter here because ATS actually uses them.
For Professional Experience, write clear points with an action verb, what you did, and why it mattered. Add metrics only where they make sense. Embedded links are great for showing proof of work.
If you‚Äôre early in your journey, Academic Projects become important. Use action verbs, mention the tools you used, and highlight the impact. No need to force numbers.
End with Relevant Projects or Volunteering. Hackathons, open source, and community work show how you collaborate and grow outside your job.

Most Cloud Network Engineers start with a Bachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs degree in fields such as (though not always mandatory): ‚Ä¢ Electronics & Telecom ‚Ä¢ Computer Networks ‚Ä¢ Computer Science
Top 3 Skills That Get You Hired
OS-level Networking Basics ‚Äì Understand the OSI model, IP, TCP, DNS, routing, and switching.
Firewall & Security Tools ‚Äì Work with firewalls, NAT, VPNs, and load balancers to secure and manage network traffic.
Cloud-native Networking ‚Äì Learn VPCs, Transit Gateway, PrivateLink, and hybrid connectivity in cloud platforms. Infrastructure as Code ‚Äì Use tools like Terraform to automate and manage cloud networks.

item.title: I NEVER Thought This Would Happen To Me! | Vishakha Sadhwani
item.description:
Vishakha Sadhwani: I NEVER Thought This Would Happen To Me! | Vishakha Sadhwani
I was the quiet, underconfident middle child who never imagined she‚Äôd end up in big tech, let alone in a different country.
And if you saw where I am today, you might think I always had everything figured out. But the truth is‚Ä¶ my entire career started because of one unexpected moment.
I missed my DU application deadline. A form didn‚Äôt reach on time, and the path I had planned for years disappeared overnight.
What felt like a massive failure back then quietly pushed me toward engineering‚Ä¶ and then toward opportunities I never would‚Äôve considered if life had gone ‚Äúaccording to plan.‚Äù
By my third year, I realised I wanted more than the predictable path everyone around me was taking. So I prepared on my own, took my exams, and moved to the U.S. for my Master‚Äôs.
That one decision changed everything.
It led me to three job offers after graduation, to AWS, to Google New York, to global conferences, to recognition from major publications, to the EB1A visa, and eventually to NVIDIA in California. It also helped me build a community of thousands of people who support me every day.
And all of this came from a moment I once thought was the end of my plans.
Sometimes the door that closes‚Ä¶ is the one that makes space for something bigger.

item.title: Robin Hood
item.description:
A new show has been added to showRSS: Robin Hood.

Robin Hood¬†is described as a sweeping, romantic adventure, a modern take of the classic tale that brings historical authenticity, psychological depth, and a heightened focus on the relationship between Rob and Marian.

In the series, following the Norman invasion of England, Rob ‚Äì a Saxon forester's son ‚Äì and Marian, the daughter of a Norman lord ‚Äì fall in love and work together to fight for justice and freedom. As Rob rises as the leader of a band of rebel outlaws, Marian infiltrates the power at court, as both work together to thwart royal corruption and bring peace to the land.
